  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Piping Engineer",
  "description": "<p><br /></p><p><strong>Mechanical  Piping Engineer</strong></p><ul><li>Review machinery and equipment specifications to ensure compliance with technical requirements.</li></ul><ul><li>Interpret classification rules and standards to address review comments and    regulatory requirements.</li><li>Demonstrate familiarity with equipment specifications and installation requirements, including main engines, generators, propulsion systems, gearboxes,hydraulic equipment, HVAC, refrigeration, and related systems.</li><li>Possess  strong knowledge of marine piping systems such as bilge, ballast, tank gauging, cooling, fuel oil, sanitary and fire protection systems.</li><li>Select appropriate pump types, compressors, pipe materials, wall thicknesses, valves and pipe fittings to meet pressure ratings and functional   requirements.</li><li>Working with a team of engineers to develop the detail 3D ship model for production. Job involving interfacing and clash check on routing of pipe systems, HVAC, electrical system installation and others.</li><li>Generate MTO for pipe routing, fittings and pipe spool for production.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualification:-</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor's degree in marine engineering or diploma in marine engineering</p><p>2. At least 5 years relevant working experience in shipyard<br />3. Proficiency in AutoCAD<br />4. Good computer skills<br />5. Understand shipbuilding and project processes. Able to comprehend the technical specification and discuss projects with customers.<br />6. Analytical ability<br />7. Communication skills<br />8. Interpersonal skills<br />9. Required to travel to Batam or other countries for technical meeting when necessary</p>",
